<h2>How to avoid spreading the flu</h2>

<p>The germs that cause flu survive on your hands and surfaces (like tables and door handles) so you should:</p>

<ul>
  <li>wash your hands with warm water and soap regularly</li>
  <li>use tissues to trap germs when you cough or sneeze</li>
  <li>bin used tissues as quickly as possible</li>
</ul>

<p>You’re most likely to spread the flu to other people in the first 5 days.</p>

<h2>How to prevent flu</h2>

<p>There is a flu vaccine that reduces the risk of catching flu and spreading it to others.</p>

<p>Flu vaccinations are usually available during flu season - December to March.</p>

